  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3e1cd92da80c7495a8fe7eb91fa80c2f, type: 3}
  m_Name: Date_Palm
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Plants.PlantData
  displayName: Date Palm
  audioClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 20c35e3758508c64294a328186a132ba, type: 3}
  environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  poem:
    text: "Draxt \u012B \u0100s\u016Br\u012Bg ( \"The Babylonian Tree\")\n\nIn X'anirala
      land \nthere is no tree of my stature. \nBecause the kings eat of me \nwhen
      I bear first fruits. \nI am the plank for boats; \nI am the mast for sails.
      \nThey make brooms of me \nwhich sweep house and home \nThey make presses of
      me \nwhich pound barley and rice. \nI am shoes for farmers; \nI am cushions
      for the barefoot. \nThey make ropes of me \nwhich bind thy legs. \nThey make
      clubs of me \nwhich break thy neck. \nThey make pegs of me \nwhich hang thee
      head downwards. \nI am fuel for fires \nwhich they roast thy flesh. \nIn summer 
      am shade \nover the head of rulers \nI am vinegar for farmers, \nhoney for
      noblemen. \nam a nest for little birds \nshade for travellers. \nEven those
      persons \nwho have neither wine nor bread \neat fruit from me \nuntil they
      become full"
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  contextInfos:
  - text: In the Poem, a date Palm and a goat argue About who is worth more to humans
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: Cultivated there since at least 4000 BCE, it was considered the tree of
      life across the ancient Persia
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: Across the near east and mediterranean it spread, withstanding the harsh
      desert Climate and dry nature
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: 'Plutarch Table Talk:

      But the palm-tree, which sheds none of the
      leaves that grow on it, is truly always in leaf, and it is this strength that
      it has which people particularly associate with the vigour that brings victory.'
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: "\"Psalm 92-12\n12 The righteous will flourish like a palm tree,\nthey
      will grow like a cedar of Lebanon;\n13 planted in the house of the Lord,\nthey
      will flourish in the courts of our God.\n14 They will still bear fruit in old
      age,\nthey will stay fresh and green,\n15 proclaiming, \u201CThe Lord is upright;\nhe
      is my Rock, and there is no wickedness in him.\u201D\""
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: in southern Iran, Palms are to this day counted not in Units but in persons.
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
